# carmel EDR intent coordination

**Canonical:** [docs/CARMEL_ENDPOINT_EDR_COORDINATION_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/CARMEL_ENDPOINT_EDR_COORDINATION_SSOT.md)

## Before running high-risk carmel scripts

1. **Log intent** (wired in scripts; agents may also run explicitly):
   `./scripts/carmel-edr-intent-log.sh --script <name> --class <pcap_capture|l2_neighbor_scan|wifi_diag|path_trace|https_smoke> --reason "…" [--domains a,b] [--ips …]`
2. **Tell the operator** which Microsoft Defender alerts may appear (3592 → **arp-scan**; curl bursts → readiness/watch/TLS; **20.190.x** → Entra/M365 split tunnel).
3. **sudo / PCAP / cloudflared login** — print exact commands for **Integrated Terminal** only; do not hang Agent on sudo.
4. **1Password** — follow [ONEPASSWORD_CLI_SESSION_GATE_SSOT.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/ONEPASSWORD_CLI_SESSION_GATE_SSOT.md) **§3**; never request secrets in chat.

## After an alert

- Correlate timestamp with `state/edr-automation-intent.jsonl`
- Optional: `./scripts/carmel-macos-security-log-tail.sh`
- Update [docs/reports/CARMEL_EDR_ALERT_TRIAGE-20260522.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/repository-restructuring/blob/main/docs/reports/CARMEL_EDR_ALERT_TRIAGE-20260522.md) only when new alert IDs appear
